                <p> </p>
                <p>The following describes the structure of the Mishnah, to be referenced by xml:id.
                    The Mishnah is divided into six orders, each divided into tractates, each of
                    which is further divided into chapters and mishnayot (mishnahs). Full references
                    to an individual section uses the following system:
                    ref.order.tractate.chapter.mishnah. Order and tractate refs are numerical and
                    follow the outline below. By convention, references to chapter and mishnah are
                    numerical. When looking up a specific witness, "ref." is replaced by the
                    relevant /TEI/teiHeader/fileDesc/sourceDesc/listWit/witness@xml:id</p>
                <p/>
